BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Annual Portland Sourdough Showcase
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T160000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T160000
UID:78af72e8@steelportknife.com
DESCRIPTION:
LOCATION:The STEELPORT Knife Co. Factory\, at 3602 NE Sandy Blvd. Portland
  Join us for the second annual "National Sourdough Day" celebration\, feat
 uring Portland's best bakers selling and sampling product\, and sharing th
 eir expertise\, including: Flour Market Dos Hermanos Cafe Olli Little T Ba
 ker Bauman's on Oak Dappled Tonic Ken's Artisan Bakery + Pizza Annex Bob's
  Red Mill Some of our bakers will even be bringing their prized sourdough 
 starters! Come enjoy food\, drinks\, shopping\, and community building\, p
 lus STEELPORT factory tours\, a raffle\, and more. The STEELPORT Knife Co.
  factory is a recommended stop for culinary professionals\, home cooks\, v
 isiting chefs and out-of-town guests searching for unique culinary and mak
 er experiences in Portland. One of Portland’s most distinctive maker des
 tinations\, blending culinary culture with American craftsmanship\, STEELP
 ORT is an active knife manufacturing floor\, as well as a retail storefron
 t\, event venue\, and educational space. Located at 3602 NE Sandy Blvd. in
  Northeast Portland \, bridging the Hollywood and Laurelhurst neighborhood
 s\, the STEELPORT Factory is open to the public Monday through Saturday fr
 om 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. The STEELPORT Factory also hosts monthly chef-led Knif
 e Skills Demos\, as well as curated artisan marketplace events throughout 
 the year. Sign up for the STEELPORT newsletter for invitations to upcoming
  events
URL:https://www.steelportknife.com/blogs/events/apr-1-2nd-annual-portland-
 sourdough-showcase
X-SOURCE:Steelport Knife Co.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Chef Demo: Peter Cho - Han Oak
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260425T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260425T110000
UID:7105cba9@steelportknife.com
DESCRIPTION:
LOCATION:STEELPORT Knife Co. 3602 Northeast Sandy Boulevard #Suite B Portl
 and\, OR 97232 Born in Korea and raised in Oregon\, Peter Cho has become a
  defining voice in Portland’s food scene. After graduating from the Univ
 ersity of Oregon\, he spent 12 years in New York City working his way up t
 o executive chef and director within a Michelin-starred restaurant group. 
 In 2016\, Cho and his wife\, Sun Young Park\, returned to Oregon and opene
 d Han Oak\, their Korean-American restaurant set inside their home\, follo
 wed by Toki in 2021. In 2023\, they opened Jeju\, a wood-fired Korean barb
 ecue restaurant centered on whole-animal butchery and locally sourced\, su
 stainably raised ingredients. Across his restaurants\, Cho blends traditio
 n with innovation while fostering mentorship and learning for emerging che
 fs. We’re excited to welcome Peter to STEELPORT\, where he’ll demonstr
 ate the knife skills central to Korean cuisine and prepare samples of a di
 sh for everyone to enjoy. RSVP below for a chance to win
URL:https://www.steelportknife.com/blogs/events/apr-25th-chef-demo-peter-c
 ho-han-oak
X-SOURCE:Steelport Knife Co.
END:VEVENT
